Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Trapezoid-shaped mummy breast cover with from top to bottom: a winged solar disc framed by two falcon heads; a wesekh-collar; a scene depicting four mummiform deities facing right: Nut (?), Isis, Osiris and Nephthys. The background is black-brown and the contours are black.
